}                            
```  This way, you hide delegation completely by creating an empty or abstract class (IDepartment) which only contains the methods that need to be hidden from outside world and then implement it in your Department classes using interface reference instead of implementing them directly as they are not necessary. It's a common practice for hiding delegate calls when dealing with complex objects, like delegation between different parts or components within an application (like database access).

